<HEADLINE>Kidnapped Russian MP found dead</HEADLINE>
<EDITION>3</EDITION>
<PAGE>6</PAGE>
<RECORDNO>980041875</RECORDNO>
<TEXT>
MOSCOW: A kidnapped Russian MP has been found dead near Moscow,
handcuffed and shot in the head. Sergei Skorochkin, 33, seized on
Wednesday by four gunmen posing as police officers, was the third
Russian MP to be killed in 10 months. Skorochkin shocked Parliament last
summer when he shot and killed an alleged Mafia attacker. A passer-by
was also killed in the shoot-out. Yesterday Skorochkin was reported to
have been hiding in London until recently.
</TEXT>
