<DOCNO>GH950203-000006</DOCNO>
<DOCID>GH950203-000006</DOCID>
<DATE>950203</DATE>
<HEADLINE>Motorsport</HEADLINE>
<EDITION>3</EDITION>
<PAGE>46</PAGE>
<RECORDNO>980041876</RECORDNO>
<TEXT>
LOTUS face a battle to hang on to one of their most prized remaining
assets -- Finnish driver Mika Salo -- as they formulate plans for a
return to Formula One in 1996.
Salo signed a new contract for the now defunct Lotus team after last
season's Japanese Grand Prix, but has since agreed an optional deal with
Tyrrell.
The issue will be settled by the Formula One contract recognition
board in Switzerland on Sunday, who last met in December to settle a
dispute between Williams and McLaren over the future of David Coulthard.
</TEXT>
