<TEXT>
NICK Faldo, playing his very first round at Poppy Hills, scored a fine
66, which included an eagle and five birdies, to leave himself one
stroke behind Davis Love after the first round of the $1.4m AT &amp; T
National Pro-Am here at Pebble Beach, California, yesterday.
The former world No.1 opened with two birdies, hitting the green at
the long first and just missing an eagle 12-footer. He sank a birdie
20-footer on the short second but then missed three putts of inside 18
feet before reaching the green at the 500-yard ninth with two drivers.
He holed out from 12 feet for an eagle 3 to turn in 32.
He dropped a shot at the tenthbut charged in a birdie eight-footer at
the short eleventh and gained two more birdies on the fifteenth and
sixteenth. Leading scores:
