<HEADLINE>Rural Scotland paper in autumn</HEADLINE>
<EDITION>3</EDITION>
<PAGE>23</PAGE>
<GRAPHIC>ILLUS</GRAPHIC>
<RECORDNO>980041885</RECORDNO>
<TEXT>
SCOTTISH Secretary Ian Lang has announced that a White Paper on rural
Scotland will be published in the autumn. In a Parliamentary answer, he
said the time was right to review rural policies.
It is almost three years since the publication of The Scottish Office
Rural Framework, which outlined a new approach to the development of
rural policy in Scotland. Mr Lang recalled that the report emphasised
the Government's commitment to ensuring that the needs of rural
communities were met in a way which reflected their distinctive and
diverse character.
''It is now an appropriate moment to review our rural policies, and
the machinery we have in place for delivering them. I intend to report
the outcome of that review in a White Paper to the published in the
autumn,'' he said.
</TEXT>
