<HEADLINE>New hit-man for Flyers</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>NIGEL DUNCAN</BYLINE>
<EDITION>3</EDITION>
<PAGE>47</PAGE>
<RECORDNO>980041888</RECORDNO>
<TEXT>
AMBITIOUS Fife Flyers last night confirmed the signing of former
National Hockey League hit-man Laurie Bochman, who has more than 1000
games under his belt in the world's top league.
Kirkcaldy rink manager John Brady said: ''This is the signing coup of
the season.''
The 34-year-old Bochman spent eight years with Winnipeg, two with New
Jersey, and a year each at Edmonton and Ottawa, logging 2020 sin bin
minutes in 1009 games.
Doug Smail, who makes his comeback for the club tomorrow after a
five-month lay-off caused by business committments, is a friend of
Bochman and helped clinch the deal.
Bochman hung up his skates in the NHL in 1993, but has kept in trim
playing recreational hockey. The 6ft 1in, 185lb powerhouse will jet in
at the end of this month, and Brady added: ''We've had a tremendous crop
of injuries and need cover until the end of the season.
''Laurie is a quality player and will strengthen our bid to win the
British championship for the first time in nine years.''
</TEXT>
