<DOCID>GH950203-000038</DOCID>
<DATE>950203</DATE>
<HEADLINE>Amos, Hogg set up Gala</HEADLINE>
<EDITION>3</EDITION>
<PAGE>46</PAGE>
<RECORDNO>980041908</RECORDNO>
<TEXT>
Gala 43, Haddington 18,
GALA coach Johnny Brown was the first to pay tribute to second
division Haddington, who never gave up in the Netherdale rain last night
and came back with two late tries from Paul Lees and Neville Ross.
Earlier, Gala had made life difficult for them on a greasy pitch,
scoring seven tries, and it could have been more.
The driving play of John Amos, and Robert Hogg's vital lineout takes,
proved the main difference.
Haddington had only a Bryan Craig drop goal and penalty to show for
their earlier efforts.
Gala's first-half tries came from prop Gary Isaac (two), Mark
Moncrieff, and Brian Swan. Later, flanker Mark Ballantyne went over
twice and Tom Weir once, and Changleng converted two tries in each half.
</TEXT>
