<HEADLINE>Daly's iron irony</HEADLINE>
<EDITION>3</EDITION>
<PAGE>44</PAGE>
<RECORDNO>980041914</RECORDNO>
<TEXT>
JOHN Daly admitted he had made a mistake by using irons off the tee
following an opening 80 in the Heineken Classic yesterday in Perth,
Australia.
The six-bogey, two double-bogey nightmare left him 14 shots off the
pace, but the controversial American took the setback calmly.
''I tried hard all the way around,'' he said, and vowed to return to
his familiar big-hitting role with the driver today at The Vines resort.
Daly said he wanted to put his stormy past behind him. ''We all make
mistakes. I just want to get on with my life and hopefully play some
good golf this year,'' he said.
''Beer and alcohol is everywhere we play and being a golfer and an
alcoholic is not the easiest thing.''
