<DOCID>GH950203-000062</DOCID>
<DATE>950203</DATE>
<HEADLINE>Rangers Catholics</HEADLINE>
<EDITION>3</EDITION>
<PAGE>18</PAGE>
<ARTICLETYPE>CORRESPONDENCE</ARTICLETYPE>
<RECORDNO>980041932</RECORDNO>
<TEXT>
January 28.
I would suggest that as the only quality newspaper representing the
West of Scotland you owe the duty of accuracy to your Glasgow
readership, including the 44,000 or so who spend every second Saturday
supporting the efforts of Rangers FC.
On this basis it was insulting to the memory of Messrs Lafferty,
McCallum, Dunbar, Tutty, Kyle, Kivlichan, McGhie, Mainds, Murray, Brown,
Jackson, Donnachie, Blyth, Kitchenbrand, and O'Neill to suggest that
John Spencer was the first Catholic footballer to be signed by Rangers
(January 28).
Worse was to follow in the suggestion that Spencer's career at Ibrox
was blighted by his religion: what of the #4m paid for Messrs Johnston
and Boli, not to mention Kuznetsov and Mikhailichenko. Still, don't let
the facts get in the way of a good stereotype.
Thomas L Ross,
7 Buchlyvie Road,
Ralston.
</TEXT>
