<HEADLINE>Chewing it over</HEADLINE>
<EDITION>3</EDITION>
<PAGE>18</PAGE>
<ARTICLETYPE>CORRESPONDENCE</ARTICLETYPE>
<RECORDNO>980041935</RECORDNO>
<TEXT>
January 27.
Could the sentiment, ''Ou est Cantona?'', (Ken Smith's Diary, January
27) be applied to James Traynor in relation to the successful Celtic
share issue?
James Traynor has been one of the main critics of Fergus McCann's
business plan, particularly his comments in the aftermath of the
Coca-Cola Cup final. He now seems to have no comment to make. Is this
because, like most sports writers, he is still chewing on his own words?
Paul Doherty,
316 Warriston Street,
Glasgow.
