<DOC>
<DOCNO>GH950203-000098</DOCNO>
<DOCID>GH950203-000098</DOCID>
<DATE>950203</DATE>
<HEADLINE>Unrest fear for Dresden date</HEADLINE>
<EDITION>3</EDITION>
<PAGE>6</PAGE>
<RECORDNO>980041968</RECORDNO>
<TEXT>
BONN: Security officials in Saxony have warned that neo-Nazi marches
and counter-demonstrations by left-wing groups are likely to take place
in Dresden on February 13, the anniversary of the 1945 Allied
firebombing which killed at least 35,000 people. The Duke of Kent and a
delegation from Coventry, which was also destroyed in the war, will
represent Britain at commemoration events.
</TEXT>
