<TEXT>
KINGSTON: Jamaica yesterday began a year-long celebration of what
would have been reggae superstar Bob Marley's 50th birthday. A four-day
concert staged by the Bob Marley Foundation featuring Bunny Wailer,
co-founder of Marley's band, began yesterday, while Prime Minister P J
Patterson is to declare Monday ''Bob Marley Day'' on the island. Marley
died in 1981 of cancer.
