<HEADLINE>Waterloo lion propped up</HEADLINE>
<EDITION>3</EDITION>
<PAGE>6</PAGE>
<RECORDNO>980042024</RECORDNO>
<TEXT>
BRUSSELS: Erosion has undermined the Lion of Waterloo, symbol of the
battle in which the Duke of Wellington routed Napoleon Bonaparte. A
Belgian Government official denied that the lion was in danger of
toppling from its pedestal overlooking the battlefield outside Brussels,
but added that #640,000 would be spent to firm it up with metal piles in
time for 180th anniversary celebrations in June.
