<HEADLINE>Police pass on Cantona file</HEADLINE>
<EDITION>3</EDITION>
<PAGE>3</PAGE>
<RECORDNO>980042028</RECORDNO>
<TEXT>
POLICE files relating to incidents allegedly involving Manchester
United footballers Eric Cantona and Paul Ince have been handed to
prosecutors, Scotland Yard said yesterday.
The documents, which contain witness statements, film footage, and
press photographs from last month's game against Crystal Palace at
Selhurst Park were sent to the Crown Prosecution Service.
A police spokesman said: ''To date, 40 statements have been taken. The
media have also responded positively to requests for film footage and
photographs of the incident.''
