<HEADLINE>Plant hire firm calls in receivers</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>ELIZABETH BUIE</BYLINE>
<EDITION>3</EDITION>
<PAGE>3</PAGE>
<RECORDNO>980042029</RECORDNO>
<TEXT>
THE Glasgow-based firm Adam Bruce Plant Hire Ltd has called in the
receivers. Established for more than 25 years, the company currently
employs 100 people.
It hires out plant and earth-moving equipment to the civil
engineering, open-cast mining, landfill, and heavy construction
industries in Scotland and North of England from its main base at
Tollcross.
Receiver Blair Nimmo, of KPMG, said yesterday: ''I feel very confident
we can find a buyer, although we cannot be sure. We have been reassuring
employees and customers that it is business as usual.''
He added: ''Adam Bruce is well known in the industries where it
operates and currently has a number of contracts with major players in
the UK market. The problem for them has been the progressive effect of
the recession on customers plus ever-increasing competitive pressures.''
</TEXT>
